blockers.body:
`db.users.findOne()` returns null when no user is found, but line 11-18
unconditionally access properties like `user.id`, `user.firstName`, etc.
This will throw "Cannot read property 'id' of null" when userId doesn't exist.
Fix: Add null check after line 9:
if (!user) {
throw new Error(`User ${userId} not found`);
}

